remarks.format:
## Remarks

`SKPathBuilder` provides a mutable, incremental API for constructing an
<xref:SkiaSharp.SKPath>. Rather than modifying the path in place, the builder
accumulates drawing commands (move-to, line-to, curve-to, arcs, and whole
shapes) and then produces a copy of the accumulated path contours as an `SKPath`.

Use <xref:SkiaSharp.SKPathBuilder.Snapshot> to obtain a copy of the path at any
time without resetting the builder, or <xref:SkiaSharp.SKPathBuilder.Detach> to
transfer ownership of the path and reset the builder in a single step.

`SKPathBuilder` is a native resource and must be disposed when no longer needed.
Always use a `using` statement or call `Dispose()` explicitly.

## Examples

```csharp
using var builder = new SKPathBuilder();
builder.MoveTo(10, 10);
builder.LineTo(100, 10);
builder.LineTo(100, 100);
builder.Close();

using var path = builder.Detach();
canvas.DrawPath(path, paint);
```
